      "content": "it's more than just old lot lines though. i was looking at the way the spire on that one building in the financial district aligns perfectly with the angle of the street and a specific monument in london. if u look at the geometry, it’s almost like a huge, invisible web connecting these specific points across the ocean. it's too precise to be just \"historical development.\" does that even sound possible to u? like a hidden layer of design?",
